asymmetric mobility SE1E2IIaR

asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar.Rd

For more information, look at vignette("commuter_model","spread")

asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar(se1e2iiar_pop = spread::asymmetric_mobility_dummy_se1e2iiar_pop,
  mobility_matrix = spread::asymmetric_mobility_dummy_se1e2iiar_mobility_matrix,
  dynamic_seeds = NULL,
  betas = spread::asymmetric_mobility_dummy_se1e2iiar_betas,
  latent_period = 2, presymptomatic_period = 3,
  infectious_period = 5, presymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 1.25,
  asymptomatic_prob = 0.4, asymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 0.5,
  N = 1)

Arguments

se1e2iiar_pop

Data frame containing `location_code`, `S`, `E1`, `E2`, `I`, `Ia`, and `R` for the entire population
mobility_matrix

List (1 entry for each time period) with each entry containing a data frame with `from`, `to`, `n` for the number of people who travel. Each data frame must be complete.
dynamic_seeds

Data.table containing `location_code`, `day`, and `n` for dynamic seeding (or `NULL`)
betas

Vector (1 entry for each time period). Float, infection parameter, 0.6
latent_period

Float, 2.0
presymptomatic_period

Float 3.0
infectious_period

Float, 5.0
presymptomatic_relative_infectiousness

Float, relative infectiousness of presymptomatic
asymptomatic_prob

Float, Proportion/probability of asymptomatic given infectious
asymptomatic_relative_infectiousness

Float, Relative infectiousness of asymptomatic infectious
N

Int = 1 int, Number of internal simulations (average taken). This is generally used for parameter fitting.

Value

A data.table containing the following variables:

location_code

Location code

week

Week number

day

Day number

time

Time of reporting (23:59)

b_S

Susceptibles belonging to location code

b_E1

E1s belonging to location code

b_E2

E2s belonging to location code

b_I

Infectious (symptomatic) belonging to location code

b_Ia

Infectious (asymptomatic) belonging to location code

b_R

Recovered belonging to location code

c_S

Susceptibles currently in this location code

c_E1

E1s currently in this location code

c_E2

E2s currently in this location code

c_I

Infectious (symptomatic) currently in this location code

c_Ia

Infectious (asymptomatic) currently in this location code

c_R

Recovered currently in this location code

c_symp_incidence

Transition from E2 to I currently in this location code

c_asymp_incidence

Transition from E1 to Ia currently in this location code

Examples

spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar(
  se1e2iiar_pop = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_se1e2iiar_pop,
  mobility_matrix = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_mobility_matrix,
  dynamic_seeds = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_dynamic_seeds,
  betas = spread::asymmetric_mobility_se1e2iiar_dummy_betas,
  latent_period = 2.0,
  presymptomatic_period = 3.0,
  infectious_period = 5.0,
  presymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 1,
  asymptomatic_prob = 0,
  asymptomatic_relative_infectiousness = 0,
  N = 1
)
